contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:07.486 --> 01:09.653
Uh, excuse me,
you don't have an appointment.

01:09.738 --> 01:10.804
I don't need an appointment.

01:10.856 --> 01:12.573
Sit down, shut up,
and listen.

01:12.641 --> 01:15.459
Harvey might forgive you because
you returned those recordings,

01:15.544 --> 01:16.427
but I don't.

01:16.511 --> 01:17.761
- Donna.
- Not done.

01:17.846 --> 01:19.980
What Harvey did with Gillis,
it was harsh,

01:20.048 --> 01:22.900
but using what I told you
in a private conversation--

01:22.984 --> 01:25.052
that crosses a line
that even Harvey never would.

01:25.120 --> 01:26.787
- Donna.
- Still not done.

01:26.838 --> 01:29.857
When you left our firm,
you left me too,

01:29.924 --> 01:32.359
but I honestly thought
that we'd always be friends.

01:32.410 --> 01:35.362
Now I'm not so sure.

01:35.413 --> 01:37.264
Amy, did you send Donna
the package?

01:37.332 --> 01:38.832
Guilt gift.
Didn't open it.

01:38.884 --> 01:41.135
It was a balenciaga
classic town bag.

01:41.203 --> 01:42.203
Ivory?

01:42.270 --> 01:43.591
Anthracite
with an outside pocket.

01:43.622 --> 01:44.655
His idea or yours?

01:44.739 --> 01:45.956
Don't answer that.

01:46.041 --> 01:49.343
It was yours.

01:49.411 --> 01:50.578
I'm sorry, Donna.

01:50.645 --> 01:52.279
You and Harvey want to
knock each other out,

01:52.347 --> 01:54.281
you go right ahead.

01:54.349 --> 01:56.450
But don't ever
betray me again.

01:59.037 --> 02:00.037
Nice shoes.

02:04.009 --> 02:05.459
She's even better
than I imagined.

02:17.906 --> 02:20.824
Looking for this?

02:20.909 --> 02:23.194
Harvey Specter.

02:23.278 --> 02:25.696
What brings you to Montclair
at 7:00 in the morning?

02:25.780 --> 02:27.614
Oh, you know
what brings me here.

02:27.666 --> 02:30.417
I woke up to find these
on my welcome mat.

02:30.485 --> 02:33.020
Well, as much as I'd love
to have been responsible

02:33.071 --> 02:36.156
for subpoenaing seven
of your firm's top clients,

02:36.208 --> 02:38.425
I didn't even know about this
till just now.

02:38.493 --> 02:40.613
You didn't even have the balls
to come at me directly.

02:40.629 --> 02:42.263
Get off my property.

02:42.330 --> 02:43.514
What's the matter, Eric?

02:43.598 --> 02:46.116
You're afraid
I'll get you fired again?

02:46.201 --> 02:48.101
I get it.

02:48.153 --> 02:50.871
You want to hear me say
I'm using my new position

02:50.922 --> 02:52.739
to destroy your business,

02:52.791 --> 02:55.259
'cause you're the piece
of garbage that got me fired.

02:55.343 --> 02:56.810
Isn't that what you
want to hear me say?

02:56.878 --> 02:59.313
Oh, I know
you'll never say that,

02:59.364 --> 03:01.031
but I do want you to admit
that you sent

03:01.116 --> 03:03.117
an agent Brian Harris
after my firm.

03:03.168 --> 03:05.002
Sorry.
I don't even have jurisdiction

03:05.086 --> 03:06.520
over that department.

03:06.588 --> 03:09.173
That department's run by a man
name Sean Cahill.

03:09.257 --> 03:10.457
So all on his own,

03:10.508 --> 03:13.010
Sean Cahill just happened
to target my firm?

03:13.094 --> 03:15.095
Well, he is a killer attorney

03:15.163 --> 03:17.948
with a nose for sleazy lawyers,

03:18.033 --> 03:19.266
and I should know.

03:19.317 --> 03:21.201
We came up together
at the Justice Department.

03:21.269 --> 03:23.404
You know, that little
governmental agency

03:23.455 --> 03:24.822
that protects their own?

03:24.906 --> 03:26.874
Well, Eric, your big brother
couldn't protect you

03:26.941 --> 03:28.208
from getting fired before,

03:28.276 --> 03:30.878
and I don't see how this is
gonna be any different,

03:30.945 --> 03:34.048
and by the way,
that's yesterday's paper.

03:35.500 --> 03:37.084
You wanted to see me?

03:37.135 --> 03:38.135
Sure did.

03:38.136 --> 03:40.287
Have a seat.

03:40.338 --> 03:42.289
I was going over
our trade sheets.

03:42.340 --> 03:43.974
Couldn't help but notice

03:44.059 --> 03:46.260
you bought another 100,000
shares of Gillis Industries.

03:46.311 --> 03:47.478
It's gonna be fine.

03:47.562 --> 03:49.179
Do I look like an asshole
to you?

03:49.264 --> 03:50.630
Where the hell
did you get the money?

03:50.682 --> 03:53.100
You know where
I got the money.

03:53.151 --> 03:54.485
I bought those shares on margin.

03:54.569 --> 03:55.569
And leveraged my company.

03:55.636 --> 03:56.654
The bylaws said I can do it.

03:56.738 --> 03:58.238
I don't care
what the bylaws say,

03:58.306 --> 03:59.857
you did this without asking.

03:59.941 --> 04:01.022
Look, I know you're pissed.

04:01.026 --> 04:02.026
Oh, I'm not pissed.

04:02.110 --> 04:03.577
I've been waiting for you

04:03.644 --> 04:05.245
to have the balls
to do something like this

04:05.313 --> 04:06.313
since you got here.

04:06.331 --> 04:07.831
You raised my risk,

04:07.916 --> 04:09.796
but you also raised my reward,
and on top of it,

04:09.817 --> 04:12.419
you did it like
an investment banker,

04:12.487 --> 04:14.121
without permission.

04:17.791 --> 04:19.959
Well, thank you, Jon.

04:20.011 --> 04:22.379
Go get 'em.

04:24.432 --> 04:26.050
One more thing.
Yeah?

04:26.134 --> 04:28.769
You have a week
to de-leverage my company.

04:28.836 --> 04:30.938
If you don't,
you're out of a job.

04:34.976 --> 04:36.176
You want to explain to me why

04:36.227 --> 04:38.028
you went to Eric Woodall's house
this morning?

04:38.063 --> 04:39.530
I understand
you're bent out of shape

04:39.614 --> 04:41.065
because I stepped on
your territory--

04:41.149 --> 04:42.950
You think I give a shit
about my territory?

04:43.017 --> 04:44.417
What the hell are you doing
in here?

04:44.486 --> 04:45.567
Listen, I really don't care

04:45.570 --> 04:47.071
if you work this thing
or I do,

04:47.155 --> 04:49.206
but whoever it is has to
not be an idiot.

04:49.290 --> 04:50.991
And how, exactly,
am I an idiot?

04:51.042 --> 04:53.494
- You poked the bear.
- Eric Woodall isn't the bear.

04:53.545 --> 04:55.379
No. I am.

04:55.463 --> 04:58.365
And whatever you were
about to say, don't say it.

04:58.416 --> 05:00.667
Harvey, this is his case.

05:00.719 --> 05:02.052
It's why we brought him in,

05:02.137 --> 05:03.337
and I don't want you involved.

05:03.388 --> 05:04.388
Me?

05:04.389 --> 05:05.506
I'm the one who found out

05:05.557 --> 05:06.706
it's not Woodall
coming after us, it's--

05:06.758 --> 05:08.425
Sean Cahill.

05:08.510 --> 05:09.810
You think I didn't know that?

05:09.877 --> 05:12.262
These are my clients,
and when they call in a panic,

05:12.347 --> 05:14.264
I need to be the voice
on the other end of the line.

05:14.349 --> 05:16.550
Then be the voice
on the other end of the line,

05:16.618 --> 05:18.318
but you're not
handling the S.E.C.

05:18.386 --> 05:20.154
I'm the reason
they're coming after us.

05:20.221 --> 05:22.322
Which is why you wanted to
hire Jeff in the first place.

05:22.390 --> 05:24.108
That was before
all this became real.

05:24.192 --> 05:25.359
Now that it's happening,

05:25.410 --> 05:26.560
he doesn't want to
sit on the sidelines.

05:26.611 --> 05:27.995
Damn right I don't.

05:28.062 --> 05:30.197
Well, then find yourself
a comfortable spot on the bench,

05:30.248 --> 05:32.533
because like it or not,
Jeff's in charge.

